1.	Problem Statement: What problem does this solve?
Users may want to share health advice with each other, so this feature allows different users to post advice for others to read.


2.	User Flow: Step by step from start to finish
User logs into Health Alert.
User navigates to the Community Forum page.
The user can see exisiting posts or click "Create post" to create their own post.
The user will submit the post and it will be saved to the database.
The user will be redirected back to the forum page and will see their post appear in the list.


3.	Technical Plan (Frontend changes, Backend routes, Database changes, Files expected to be created or modified)
Frontend Changes - Make a page for the community forum where users can make posts and see other people's posts.
Files to create: .xml
Backend Changes - Must support creating posts and retrieiving posts.
Database Changes - Must store the posts users make, so will make a table for posts.


4.	API Changes (New routes, Modified routes, Request and response structure)
  1. Create Post
  request the userId, title, and the content
  response: "Post created successfully"
  2. Get All Posts
  response: postId, userId, title, the content, timestamp


5.	Database Changes (New tables, Schema updates, New fields)
New table: Posts
postId, userId, title, content, timestamp

6.	Acceptance Criteria (Clear definition of done, Must be testable)
Users are able to navigate to forum, create posts to the community forum, and read through the forum.
